modules.description: Initializes an ID3v2 tag structure and parses header and tag data from binary strings. It supports attaching text-based frames and setting metadata fields like title, artist, and album. The module renders valid tags into binary format for embedding in audio files.

Provides functions to open, close, and save files, along with retrieving and modifying metadata and audio properties. Works with file types and tagged file structures, enabling manipulation of audio file metadata and technical attributes. Used to read and write ID3 tags, extract audio duration, bitrate, sample rate, and channel count from audio files.

Handles ID3v2 tag manipulation by initializing, parsing, and rendering tag structures from binary data. It supports text-based frames and metadata fields such as title, artist, and album. Operations include extracting information from existing tags and generating new ones for embedding. Examples include modifying a track's artist name or extracting album details from a binary tag stream.

Provides functions to read and write audio metadata, including tags for ID3v1, ID3v2, and Vorbis comments. Works with audio file paths and structured metadata objects containing title, artist, album, and other common fields. Used to extract or modify metadata in MP3, FLAC, and other supported audio formats programmatically.

Manages audio file metadata and ID3 tags through functions for file handling, tag manipulation, and property extraction. Supports operations like reading and writing title, artist, and album information, as well as retrieving audio details such as duration and bitrate. Enables modification of existing tags and creation of new ones from binary data. Examples include updating a track's artist or extracting album metadata from a tag stream.
